{
  "texts": [
    "We evaluate on 897 focal methods drawn from 26 open source projects used in benchmarks in prior work [22,39].",
    "We select focal methods from these projects where Pynguin [24] (an SBST tool for Python) was unable to achieve full coverage on the focal method during 10 runs, indicating the focal method poses a challenge for existing automated test generation tools.",
    "In this dataset, Pynguin had an average line coverage of 72.4% with std. deviation of 12.7%.",
    "Evaluated Models.",
    "Following the literature on test generation with language models [3,36], we evaluate SymPrompt with a single recent open source model, CodeGen2 [27]."
  ]
}